<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870119-0144 </DOCNO><HL> Aritech Anti-Takeover Plan</HL><DD> 01/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ARIT </IN><DATELINE> FRAMINGHAM, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Aritech Corp., a maker of electronic security equipment, said it adopted an anti-takeover plan.    Under the plan, its holders will receive rights to purchase 1/100th of a share of a new issue of preferred stock for each common share held. The exercise price will be $45. The rights will be exercisable if a person or entity buys or proposes to buy 20% or more of Aritech's common stock without the company's prior consent, Aritech said. The company said it isn't aware of any takeover bids for it. </TEXT></DOC>